        &lt;br&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;tabula-py&#34;&gt;tabula-py&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/chezou/tabula-py&#34;&gt;tabula-py&lt;/a&gt; is a simple Python wrapper of tabula-java&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Installation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;pip install tabula-py
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Usage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-Python&#34; data-lang=&#34;Python&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#204a87;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;tabula&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8f5902;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;# Read pdf into list of DataFrame&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;df&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;tabula&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;read_pdf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;test.pdf&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;pages&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;all&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8f5902;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;# Read remote pdf into list of DataFrame&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;df2&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;tabula&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;read_pdf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;https://github.com/tabulapdf/tabula-java/raw/master/src/test/resources/technology/tabula/arabic.pdf&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8f5902;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;# convert PDF into CSV file&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;tabula&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;convert_into&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;test.pdf&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;output.csv&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;output_format&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;csv&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;pages&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;all&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8f5902;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;# convert all PDFs in a directory&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;tabula&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;convert_into_by_batch&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;input_directory&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;output_format&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;csv&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;pages&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;all)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;r-tabulizer&#34;&gt;R Tabulizer&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/ropensci/tabulizer&#34;&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Installation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-R&#34; data-lang=&#34;R&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;install.packages&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;tabulizer&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Usage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-R&#34; data-lang=&#34;R&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;library&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;tabulizer&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;file.path&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;directory&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;my.pdf&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;out1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ce5c00;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;extract_tables&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;f&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;str&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;out1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;note&#34;&gt;Note&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The extraction works but the results are not always good, especially when the pdf tables are not properly formatted.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

      </description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Docs: Video/Audio</title>
      <link>/docs/swiss-knives/converter/converter-video-audio/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 23 Apr 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/docs/swiss-knives/converter/converter-video-audio/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;br&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;ffmpeg&#34;&gt;ffmpeg&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;download&#34;&gt;Download&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ffmpeg.org/download.html&#34;&gt;Download zip file or exe file&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Or download from source&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;git clone https://git.ffmpeg.org/ffmpeg.git ffmpeg
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;setup&#34;&gt;Setup&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extract &lt;code&gt;ffmpeg&lt;/code&gt; from downloaded zip file if needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open terminal and go to the path of &lt;code&gt;ffmpeg &lt;/code&gt;file&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;documentation&#34;&gt;Documentation&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ffmpeg.org/documentation.html&#34;&gt;Link&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;convert-video-format&#34;&gt;Convert video format&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Convert between &lt;code&gt;mp4&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;avi&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;mkv&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;ffmpeg -i  input.avi output.mp4
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To set the video bitrate of the output file to 64 kbit/s&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;ffmpeg -i input.avi -b:v 64k -bufsize 64k output.avi
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To force the frame rate of the output file to 24 fps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;ffmpeg -i input.avi -r &lt;span style=&#34;color:#0000cf;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;24&lt;/span&gt; output.avi
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;under-the-hood&#34;&gt;Under the hood&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;ffmpeg&lt;/code&gt; calls the &lt;code&gt;libavformat&lt;/code&gt; library (containing &lt;code&gt;demuxers&lt;/code&gt;) to read input files and get packets containing encoded data from them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;When there are multiple input files, ffmpeg tries to keep them synchronized by tracking lowest timestamp on any active input stream.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;terms&#34;&gt;Terms&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;frame-rate&#34;&gt;Frame rate&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;expressed in frames per second or FPS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the frequency (rate) at which consecutive images called frames appear on a display&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the term applies equally to film and video cameras, computer graphics, and motion capture systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;frame rate may also be called the frame frequency, and be expressed in hertz.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;bit-rate&#34;&gt;Bit rate&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In telecommunications and computing, bit rate (bitrate or as a variable R) is the number of bits that are conveyed or processed per unit of time.&lt;/p&gt;

      </description>
    </item>
    
